This is long. Really long. But it's a stark reminder of how, in the Foundation universe, no one is safe from the world of anomalous effects and events; that reminder coupled with the effort put into this and the depth of the details of what occurred leads me to a very enthusiastic +1. There's nothing about this I don't like, even the supposedly cheesy occult activity; it's tonally fitting and it works in-context. Excellent work.

Edit: Oh, there is one thing I don't like, and that's the random new GoI. But its importance is so subjective that it definitely doesn't negatively affect my view of the article.





