SCP-2736-1 is Solid Nixon, and SCP-2736-2 is Liquid Nixon. They are both clones of the original, Big Senator, also known as Naked Nixon, who used his stealth skills to escape that pit undetected and now wears a cool eyepatch since they cut his eye out. It all lines up.

That aside, I think I'll novote this for now. The concept is good, and some parts of it are great, but the plot of the piece, to me, falls a bit short.  it's more of a plot hook than a beat itself. The babbling and creepy imagery don't really work for me, so I'm left with a skip that has a stable foundation, but doesn't go anywhere truly exemplary with it. It doesn't go all-out with the cult, nor with the ritual, nor with the creepiness, nor even with the characterization of either Nixon. It sort of goes halfway in every direction, so at the end I'm left with a feeling of vague unsatisfaction.







